description:
Welcome to our comfortable and peaceful home!Set in the heart of SW London, it's next to the charming Battersea Square and moments from the River Thames Walk.Its ideal location offers excellent transport links by train from Clapham Junction to central London,and buses to Sloane Square, South Kensington& Victoria.The area’s family orientated nature is owed to the nearby park's excellent offerings,plus the variety of restaurants, cafes,bars & weekly farmers market being a short walk from the door!

The space
Our apartment is well equipped with everything you might need, whilst providing a homely space to retreat back to at the end of the day. The living area has inviting comfy sofas, Sky TV and an array of books to sink your teeth into. There is also a dining area seating up to four guests to enjoy a family dinner, or quick bite before heading out to enjoy the local areas delights.

Moving onto the bedrooms- where the flats tranquil colour scheme continu
neighborhood_overview: Steps away from our front door are the restaurants and cafes of Battersea Square, including a Gordon Ramsay restaurant and our favourite independent restaurant Queenswood. The best Pizza around is from Melanzana, plus a very popular Gail's cafe. Not far from the house we have a weekly farmers market (Nutbourne Restaurant - Saturday morning 10am-2pm), a local Sourdough Bakery (Flour to the people), a local organic shop (Apples & Bees), and a great organic food store (Hoxton Fruit & Veg). This is a very family oriented area with many people commuting to the city from here daily. We walk to Battersea Park almost every day which has amazing children's playgrounds and adult sports facilities. For a more rugged outdoors time (as much as we can get in London) we go to Wimbledon Common by our local bus (170) or to Richmond Park (on the same route). A short walk away is the world famous Chelsea where you can marvel at the boutique shops and dine in the finest cafe/restaurants in the city.

name: Leafy street modern Victorian flat
description:
Old Victorian townhouse recently converted into flats. Extensively renovated, the flat boasts modern amenities throughout. 2-bedroom with 1 of them converted into a study.

Quiet street, well connected to Central, shops nearby.

The space
Part of an Victorian building, our flat maintains elements of this past while being recently refitted with modern amenities.
Our flat occupies the upper floor of an old townhouse, with the roof wedging space in several corners. An exceptional wooden floor runs throughout the space (except for bedroom which is carpeted). Large double-glazed windows provide great amount of sunlight while keeping the cold away.
Fully equipped kitchen for those who enjoy cooking, a comfy 3-seater couch invites you to a quick siesta after your meal.
The flat is decorated with a mix of vintage elements, IKEA furniture and objets trouvés in the streets of London desr to our heart.

Guest access
You'll hav
neighborhood_overview:
London is made of a number of little neighbourhoods with its own high streets and identities. We are in the middle of two of those.
Hipster Stoke Newington starts on Church Street just 3min away from our flat, running alongside Clissold Park before being packed with restaurants, pubs and shops.
Posh Highbury a longer 7min walk West, with the pub in Highbury Grange being a central landmark and shops running along Hughbury Grove.
A little further West is Highbury & Islington station, where the main commercial street of the neighbourhood (Upper Street) ends.
Be aware we are a short walk from the Arsenal football ground (Emirates stadium), so all this is a bit different when police-controlled crowds of football fans takeover Highbury.
host_about:
Ex-engineer and ex-management consultant, lived abroad and travelled extensively—yet still not enough!
Life is a continuous quest for the next thing I will not want to do anymore.

I'm a quiet guy—used to be pathologically shy, now I just prefer to be quiet when have nothing to say—while also friendly and a lover of interesting art, good food (but not necessarily "high gastronomy") and overpriced coffee. I prefer listening to some jazz to Katy Perry. Well, I prefer almost anything to listening to Katy Perry to be honest. A walking tour around London, a gig/concert at the Barbican (or St Luke's, or the Southbank), or just a coffee close to my place: you are always invited to join me!

Among other things, I'm also an amateur photographer—when I do not overthink about politics of representation (thanks for making me not want to take pictures anymore, Sontag!). Welcome to my world!

host_about:
Hi!  We are a family of four, my husband is  Martin and my children are Thomas (10) and Annabelle (8).   I have recently re-trained as an interior designer and my husband has a property development business.  We renovated our house in 2013 taking it back from 5 flats to a comfortable and warm family home in which we love spending time in together.  

My husband is a great cook and we and our children are all foodies.  You will often find us cooking and trying new things out in the kitchen or barbequing up a feast in the garden.

We are also lovers of the outdoors and make regular trips to the country to visit grandparents often taking to bike riding across the Somerset levels or skimming stones at the seaside on Hayling Island.

Sport is a big feature in our lives too, both playing and watching.  Martin and Thomas play tennis and football and are both season ticket holders of local football team QPR whilst Annabelle is enjoying her first experience of playing netball.

We are keen to make a great impression on all our Airbnb guests and help make your stay a memorable one!  So, any questions you have please don't hesitate to ask!

As you will see when you visit, from a print hanging in our home, one of our life's mottos is "Work Hard & Be Nice to People"

We look forward to welcoming you to Shepherd's Bush.

With our best wishes,

Fiona, Martin, Thomas and Annabelle.

neighborhood_overview:
“A place of great contrasts” fits Deptford perfectly. The lively high street — with a noisy, thrice-weekly market — and the artists’ enclaves.

A buzz has grown around Deptford in recent years, with the term ‘the new Peckham’ being thrown around frequently in reference to the relatively low rents, lively, creative community and urban cool atmosphere that can be found here. As always, the creatives have brought a series of hip restaurants, independent shops and cool coffee cafes with them, and as Peckham’s star rapidly begins to rise the developers are now coming in droves.

The heart of Deptford is its long high street, stretching from Deptford Broadway to Creek Road. There is a busy market on Wednesdays, Fridays and Saturdays selling everything from clothes to fish, fruit and vegetables. The market strays into Douglas Way, where there is bric-a-brac for sale, and street food stalls trade on Saturdays in Giffin Square next to the new library and Tidemill Academy.

description:
Situated by the Regent’s Canal, this apartment offers an impressive roof terrace and space for up to 4 adults, 1 child and 1 infant. Just 20 minutes from Soho and the centre of London and just 15 minutes from King’s Cross St Pancras for connections to the Eurostar.

The space
There is an elevator up to the entrance of the apartment, which is situated on the 2nd floor of the building.

KITCHEN, DINING AND LIVING ROOM
The kitchen and dining space is contemporary in style. It includes all the amenities you will need for your stay. The room includes a dining table and seating by the window, as well as an ochre yellow sofa and armchair. There is also a television, artwork on the walls and access out to the balcony.

BALCONY
On the balcony there is a small table and chairs in green, as well as views to the surrounding area.

BATHROOM
The bathroom offers a bath, overhead shower, WC and basin, all in sleek grey tiling.
neighborhood_overview: A few minutes from this home, you can walk along the Regent’s Canal, for riverside cafes and pretty surroundings. Angel itself has plenty of shops and eateries to enjoy. Islington’s Upper street is around a 15-minute walk from the apartment- home to a whole host of wonderful boutiques, cafes, restaurants, cinemas and theatres. Visit Ottolenghi’s renowned restaurant for a taste of the Mediterranean or head to Mem and Laz Brasserie for great food and atmosphere. King’s Cross is also close by; we recommend visiting Granary Square and Coal’s Drop Yard for a taste of this area- around a 25 minute walk away. Also in the area is Old Street, Hoxton and Shoreditch- for great coffee shops, graffiti art tours and independent shops.

description:
An ensuite room in a canal-side apartment in the coolest part of London! Canal walks, right next door to Olympic Park and Victoria Park, excellent local bars, cafes and restaurants. You'll have your own front door and bathroom, plus access to my kitchen, living room and balcony.

The space
All mod cons inc wifi, washing machine, dishwasher, stereo (but no television!) The flat is set in a secure gated development with 24 hr concierge. I like to make my guests feel comfortable; I'll make time to find out what you want from your visit, and help you to plan your trip.

Guest access

Other things to note
What Valentina, Cookiepuss*, Lady Oscar, and I offer is a chilled, open space in a sweet spot in London. We are artists. We love people, sharing, and London. We live by a canal that thrives with birds,
neighborhood_overview:
Hackney Wick is amazing, but is changing fast - buildings are going up very quickly, replacing the vibrant creative community that has lived here for fifteen years. It's like Kreuzberg in Berlin, or Williamsburg in Brooklyn in the mid 90s; it's less gentrified than most other parts of East London.
made more amazing by how it balances nature - canal walks and great cafes in parks - with a more creative edge.
host_about:
I'm an artist, born and bred in London, a city which I know intimately and love dearly.

I love Airbnb, and the sharing economy. Airbnb has seen many people from all walks of life walk through my door. For me, life will always be about learning, and enjoyment;  I enjoy the moments I can hang out with my guests, and what I can learn from these moments. 

I will be happy to advise you on your time here. It's easy to avoid the tourist traps and get to know another side of the city. 

My interests, in no particular order: friends, swimming, nature, literature, music, politics, food, theatre, sustainability, TED, comedy, education, street art, travel, poetry. My tastes in music and food are diverse, and I love sharing.

neighborhood_overview: In the heart of Southwark, minutes from London Bridge station and Tower Bridge, Borough embodies central London living at its best. The area gets its name from a time when it was the only borough outside the City of London. Beyond the jurisdiction of the City authorities, in the 16th and 17th centuries the area was a playground famed for its inns, theatres and the notorious Southwark Fair which was shut down in 1762 after being deemed too debauched. It retains enormous character in many of its buildings, streets and shops, and a great mix of cultural opportunities remain. There are famous theatres, you’re never more than a brisk walk away from wonderful pubs dating back to medieval times, and it’s home to Borough Market, the Tate Modern and Europe’s tallest building, The Shard. The added appeal of Borough to those living or working in the area is the proximity to London Bridge and Waterloo. host_about:
Greetings from the Veeve team!


Veeve manage the largest collection of homes to rent for short stays in London since 2011, launching in Paris in 2017. Our rental homes are predominantly privately-owned, lived-in homes in vibrant neighbourhoods. Thanks to our fully managed service, when you stay in a Veeve property you can benefit from the spaciousness, personal style and relaxed feel of a home – but with all the amenities of a hotel.


Once a booking is confirmed our Customer Service team will become your main point of contact and get in touch with you to organise your arrival at the property (including airport transfers, upon request); after which our on-the-ground management team will look after all aspects of your stay, with in-stay support available to help with any queries.


We have strict cleanliness guidelines for our cleaners and all staff who enter our properties and have reinforced existing cleaning procedures in line with official WHO, British and French government guidance.


As always, our team ensure that all properties are cleaned to a professional standard before and after each stay, with increased focus on touch-point cleaning (door handles, kitchen surfaces, kettles, taps etc.).

 All staff who enter properties will follow the below procedures:
 

- Carry and regularly use alcohol-based hand rub
- Sanitise their mobile phones 
- Focus extra attention when cleaning key touch-point areas (door handles, kitchen surfaces, kettles, taps etc.)
- Wear protective gear where appropriate
- Wash and disinfect work shoes


We might be able to arrange for property viewings, upon request, for stays of over 28 nights. 


If you have any questions, please do not hesitate to contact us and we will be sure to answer you promptly.
